Optional class -
  To avoid NullPointerException, we have to check if(obj != null) always to perform any 
  operation on obj. When we are calling methods-chain like
  method1().method2().method3()...., we have to check null for every object. So avoid such
  bulky code, Java 8 introduced Optional class. 
  It is used to remove the need for multiple null checks to protect against the 
  NullPointerExceptions during run-time.
  Optional is a container object used to contain not-null objects. 
  Optional object is used to represent null value as absent value. 
  
  Methods of Optional class -
  1) empty()		     - creates empty object
  2) of()                - create Optional object with non-null value. If null value passed, throws NullPointerException.  
  3) ofNullable()        - create Optional object with non-null value. If null value passed, 
                           creates empty Optional object. 
  4) get()               - converting an existing Optional to its value. If Optional is empty, 
                           throws NoSuchElementException.
  5) isPresent()         - checks if Optional contains any value. Return true if there is a value present, 
                           otherwise false.
  6) ifPresent()         - If a value is present, invoke the specified consumer with the value, otherwise do nothing.
                           Enables us to run some code on the wrapped value if it's found to be non-null.    
  7) orElse()            - Return the value if present, otherwise return other. 
                           It takes one parameter, which acts as a default value. 
                           The orElse() method returns the wrapped value if Optional is present, and if not, returns 
                           its argument.  But argument is evaluated even if Optional is present. 
  8) orElseGet()         - Same like orElse() but if the Optional is not empty, the argument is not even executed.
  9) orElseThrow()       - It returns value only if it's present. Otherwise, it'll throw an exception.
  10) ifPresentOrElse()  - Java 9 method.
                           If Optional value is present, perform some action. If not, perform some other action.
                           
